After, when the messengers of the emperor had received his bene- diction‚ they made their gear ready and departed‚ and subdued their enemies to the empire without shedding of blood, and sith returned to the emperor and were worshipfully received. And after this it happed that some other in the emperor's house had envy on the weal of these three princeS, and accused them to the emperor of high treason, and did so much by prayer and by gifts that they caused the emperor to be so full of ire that he commanded them to prison, and without other demand, he commanded that they should be slain that same night. And when they knew it by their keeper, they rent their clothes and wept bitterly; and then Nepotian remembered him how S.
